	   <tr><td colspan=2>You know what, this is a dumbass argument.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am sick of hearing the lowbies talking about how much more fun it is not to twink.  Ummm well, you wanna know something, IT DOESN'T MATTER HOW MUCH YOU TWINK CUZ AT 50+ YOU STILL AINT GONNA BE ABLE TO SOLO A BLUE!  Hell I have to use my disciplines most often to take down a light blue, or sometimes even get owned by some green mobs.  While I do respect some of the knowledge you know of the class not all of us want to play OUR game this way.  And while I understand you are not as fully knowledged in the &quot;high end game,&quot;  perhaps you should take a step back and examine that angle of EQ.  Having uber gear is pretty much the goal of the game.  The better your gear is the better you help your group/guild, the more you help them, the more you can do.  You just arent going to see a guild go straight from wearing fine plate to warlords, you have to go through steps in armor.  And as I am sure you realize this what does it really matter if you just skip a bunch of steps if you plan to play your character to 60 asap anyways?  Really and truly twinked characters can easily PL entire groups just by the awesome dmg output they have because they have gear that boosts their stats enough to where something blue is trivial.  To me it seems until you have played all aspects of the game you should stick to talking about what you know &gt;&lt;<br> <br>&nbsp;<br>~Tactikal Mizkalculation~&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>60 ASSASSIN <br>Cruxor Thunderblade<br>Level 51 gimp Paladin<br>Vazaelle<br></td></tr>
